t look like? Who will listen to the grievances of the people? Can there be another future for the region that is not the return of the security state or the continuation of monarchies? Placing developments in the Middle East in the broader context of revolutionary history, The Death of the Nation tackles these critical questions.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aArab Spring, 2010-. 0aIslam and politicszMiddle East. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016z978311066754708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016z978311065748740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520966437423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520966437.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065748-7  UCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-066754-7  UC Press eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles